suh8ru.com
Steph
SHINE... by Rev. Dr. Omolola Omoteso The Bible say, let your light so shine before all humans that they may see God in you. Matthew 5:16 This is NOT calling you to shine like others shine. This is not asking you to borrow energy from others so you can shine in the brightness of others. This is not a call for you to enter into competition or comparison so you can outshine others. This is NOT calling you to fake being a bigger or smaller light. "Fake it till you make it" is inspiration from the pit of hell but calling the things that are not as though they are is the Bible injunction that gives you permission to aspire to be better. The injunction to shine is calling you to shine at your level, in your place and your space. This is giving you permission to SHINE - shine your Christian character, shine your knowledge, shine your truth, shine your wisdom, shine your kindness, shine your skills so that others can see God in you. You are enough. Be graceful and gracious to yourself. Whether you consider your light big or small, you need to shine it to excude joy, and outshine darkness. Some lights are so strong that they can only be used in bigger spaces. Some lights are so small but awesome in locating things in pinholes. SHINE. The order to shine does NOT infer that you stay at your level of shine, it means accept your level of shine while trusting God to glow better. Give yourself liberty to leverage on the beauty and sunshine in you now as you open yourself up to God to shine brighter through you. I love YOU.

Dear One, Thanks for being a big part of the Feast of Esther ministry. God who led Queen Esther to redeem her people will divinely position you as an empire emancipator in Jesus name. One major aspect of The Feast, remain the messages by anointed ministers that reignite, restore and refresh God's anointing upon our lives as leaders. Few years ago, a compilation was added to ensure delegates and those yet to attend have the full dose of messages. This book is launched annually to fund the project. *Feast of Esther USA* is honoured to be invited to be the launcher of the Feast of Esther 2023 Book. This is a rare privilege that gives us the opportunity to sow into the past that births a new future to serve peace, progress and prosperity to beautify lives beyond our comfort zones. Isaiah 52:7, Romans 10:15 Our Country Coordinator, Pastor Grace Okonrende, has opened this opportunity to us to enable us be part of sponsoring the production of this book to be launched during the International Feast on Thursday 15th February 2024. To be part of this, kindly zelle your cash gift of any amount to +1 (832) 372-0860 with memo: The Feast Book Launch. As you sow into this work, intercede that our lives will be divinely beautified and the book will become a divine tool for salvation, deliverance, healing, restoration and redemption of souls in Jesus name. After the order of Romans 8:28 and Esther 4:14, I pray that God will cause all things to work together for good to you because you are called, at such a time as this, according to God's purpose in Jesus name. Thank YOU.

Ujb354uM.com
Steph
Pastor Omolola Odumosu Oyebade at 65! Matriach. Mother. Minister. Mentor. Midwife for destinies, including mine! I walk confidently in the shoes of my beloved namesake. Last year at the Feast of Esther USA, we had this anointed God's General as Guest Minister. She was delegated by our mother in the Lord, Mummy Foluke Adeboye. This bundle of brain and beauty who stands tall where even some male pastors balk; a great leader, counsellor and chaplain, was truthful, down to heart and shared the original unadulterated Word of God as she was sent by God. I planned to see her one on one and God said no, that I should give newer members an opportunity to do so. But God had positioned me to interact with her one on one via the newsletter I edit for The Feast. When I went to greet her, she poured out of her anointing upon me and I caught the fire. I knew God had added to my mothers in ministry. After that meeting, I experienced a new level of grace. My life is beautified by those God sends my way. Rev. Omolola is one of them. Her status posts and messages remain a blessing to my Christian walk and ministerial, missionary and chaplaincy work. Congratulations Mama!

About

Feast of Esther is an annual Feast founded and coordinated by the wife of the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God Pastor (Mrs.) Folu Adeboye. It is a vision and a divine assignment given by God. Feast of Esther is the gathering of women who are General Overseers, wives of General Overseers, Prelates, Arch Bishops and Head of Ministries. They come together to interact for the purpose of fellowship, prayer, renewal, growth, development and to stand in the gap for their churches, ministries and the nation. The Feast is a time set aside by these women to share experience and learn from each other. The first Feast of Esther was held in February 2002 and has become an annual event held at the Redemption Camp Nigeria. The Feast of Esther holds also in Nigeria, Ghana, Cote D’Ivoire, Zambia, Kenya, Malawi, Togo, Republic of Benin, South Africa, Cameroun, United Kingdom, Germany and Mainland Europe. Feast of Esther NA is for female General Overseers, wives of General Overseers and Heads of ministries in North America which includes Canada and Caribbean.
